The architects looked in - the office also includes a kindergarten
The Avriopoint office building in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch.Design.
But who would expect a mini-kindergarten here, with everything that goes with it: colorful walls, creative furniture, a lot of toys and even a mini playground on the outdoor terrace.
This kindergarten has been available to Arch.Design employees since last year.
The Arch.Design design and architecture office, whose studios come from a number of well-known Brno buildings, calculated from the first designs for the new Avriopoint building with the premises for its company mini-kindergarten.
Wisely, because most of its 90 employees are in the baby boom age and the company is committed to ensuring that the designers and architects return to their jobs as soon as possible.
Along with the opportunity to work in short, the kindergarten is another bonus that Arch.Design has to offer its employees in the concept of their social program.
This makes it easier for the civil engineers to bring their demanding profession and childcare under one roof.
The Mini Kindergarten is an original idea of Arch.Design employees and with the support of management they managed to win funding from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs for their project.
The operational mini-kindergarten is financed by the Operational Programme Human Resources and Employment Policy from the European Social Fund and from the state budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to this funding (grant of CZK 2.8 million), the necessary facilities and equipment could be procured and for the duration of 2 years is provided for qualified personnel and for the operation.
After exhausting the funding (2 years), the company Arch.Design is obliged to continue operating the Minikindergarten for another 3 years at its own expense.
The preparation of this project took a whole year, with the company Economy Rating actively assisting in the processing of applications.
The children are taken care of full-time qualified staff - a nurse and a kindergarten teacher, the kindergarten can visit children without age restrictions, although most of them are over three years old.
And since this is a mini-kindergarten, only 5 children are allowed to be present at the same time, but several children change over the day.
The kindergarten operation is flexibly tailored to the needs of the parents, the children of all employees have the same rights in terms of the use of the kindergarten - regardless of the company hierarchy and their respective position.
Although it is about individual education and care, the program content in the mini-kindergarten is nevertheless comparable to the framework program of pre-school education.
The children not only play here, but above all they are offered excellent lessons - from basic knowledge to pre-school lessons, they also learn English.
The classroom is not only equipped with toys and creative games, but also with a computer that is available to the children.
What's more - the presence of small children in the company contributes to a friendly and positive corporate environment.
Parents can take a look at the children at any time and thus eliminates the stress of late picking up the children from a distant kindergarten.
Parents therefore use their working hours more productively.
It is no wonder that there are also natural and loyal employer-employee relationships.
Arch.Design ranked among the Czech companies, which offer significant benefits in the recruitment of new employees, which are family-friendly and through such programs strengthen their personal marketing.
A bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Check out the interiors of Gaudi
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric lizard, the stairs like the spine of a dinosaur, and the balconies are torn up fish mussels.
This is the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> of the Catalan architect Antonio Gaudi in Barcelona.
From the local inhabitants, the house with its organic forms got the nickname "Knochenhaus".
Organic shapes, wild colors, the unusual use of stone, tile splitters and mosaics, the scales-like facades and ubiquitous soft lines, all these are typical features of the Art Nouveau style of Antonio Gaudi.
The facade of the house plays with dreamlike lines, delicate colors and textures reminiscent of nature and creatures.
It is only after a closer look that one notices that everything is dominated by geometry, rhythm and thought-out order.
At night, the whole fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade looks even more plastic, dramatic and the special lighting enhances the brightness of the colors.
The same oscillating lines and intricate shapes also dominate the interior of the house.
Wave-shaped wood copies the window frames, railings, decorative elements of doors, even look holes and rails.
The house Batll<0xC3><0xB3> in the Eixample district on the busy shopping street Passeig de Gr<0xC3><0xA1>cia No 43 was created by the reconstruction of a house from 1877, carried out by the architect Emilio Sala Cortese.
The reconstruction took two years and was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialist Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, initially insisted on the demolition of the old and the construction of a completely new building, but ultimately agreed to Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>'s idea of an unusual and also cheaper reconstruction.
However, the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> rental house was not designed by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> alone.
He worked with the architect Josep Maria Jujol.
It was on his drawing board that the decorations for the representative apartment of the reality owner were created, and also the use of mosaics on the facade was his idea.
However, numerous other painters and artists also worked on the design of the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade.
The joint work on the designs for Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> was the beginning of a fruitful collaboration between Jujola and Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Jujol was also involved in the construction of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s Casa Mil<0xC3><0xA1> in Park G<0xC3><0xBC>ell, which also houses other works by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Shortly after its completion, the house received from the local inhabitants its organic forms due to the nickname "Knochenhaus".
Others, in turn, called it the special window opening mechanism because of the "hanging house".
It is also said that at the top of the building is the sword of Saint George, the patron saint of Catalonia.
But also other sculptural elements symbolize hidden religious motifs.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> designed for the house a central heating system unique for the time with ventilation channels and typical fireplaces.
Something bizarre is already hinting at her 45-degree inclination.
In his work, Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> consistently ignored all the building regulations of the time and did not allow himself to be swayed by them.
Before the start of construction, he obtained the appropriate building permit from the city, but the information he provided about the planned reconstruction was so vague that two years later the city fathers were so horrified by the result when it was completed that they asked for a remedy.
Among other things, the councillors also came across the fact that the construction with its pillars even intervened in the public sidewalk.
However, there were no more changes, quite the opposite - only fifteen days after the district's request in this regard, Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3> submitted an application for permission to rent the two highest floors of the house - and it was promptly granted to him.
The house owner himself moved into the lower floors.
In the gallery on the 2nd floor was a lounge, on the third floor were the bedrooms and private rooms of the apartment.
The ground floor was leased to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey building runs through a staircase up to the roof terrace.
Due to the basic elements of the conversion, all right angles and straight lines were removed and replaced by curved and curved walls.
However, Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked with a modern concept for the mutual connection of spaces.
The social part can be completely connected by opening the salon doors and so a larger society could chat comfortably without having to give up a certain intimacy in more confidential conversations.
In addition to a new fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade, Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s renovation also gave the house a rather unusual roof and two more floors.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s play with the light as well as the blue and white glazed tiles with which the courtyard is clad and the lighthouses are also impressive.
The play of these two colors gives all floors of the house a maximum amount of light.
In doing so, he simply took advantage of the principle that white reflects light better than dark colors that absorb sunlight on the contrary.
Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, which was added to UNESCO’s World Heritage List in 2005, is open to everyone today.
On the first floor, the most spacious and magnificent apartment is made available to the public.
The owners of the house decided to take this step only in the year and this on the occasion of the 150th birthday of the famous creator.
When it was found that this is a fairly profitable business, the visits were maintained, yes, they were also extended to other common and the attic rooms, including the roof terrace.
However, the price for visiting the monument is not a cardboard stick, it is 16.50 euros, students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourist cards get a 20 percent discount.
This amount exceeds the entrance fees to other Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> buildings in the city.
If you want to get to know the real atmosphere of the house with its dragon towers, you should try to make friends with one of the house residents and visit him at home.
The right mattress and the right bedding? Women have different desires than men
Not the best bed frame, but the quality of the bedding - so mattress and rust make up the good bed.
However, these must be harmoniously complemented in order to meet the wishes of the specific user.
Many things play a role in the selection - the weight, the size, the state of health and, last but not least, the sex of the sleeper.
Equally important is the interior, in which mattress and rust have to be subordinated.
Typical example?
In a weekend house where it is not regularly heated, latex mattresses are not well suited, as they need much longer to "get warm".
In addition, they are significantly heavier than conventional polyurethane mattresses.
And - they should be turned regularly.
If they do not have enough vents in the core and are still on a solid plate, moisture accumulates: it is therefore not excluded that mold forms under them.
Of course, the choice also plays a role in what you are used to.
Who has been abroad for a long time, where very high mattresses with soft layer are common, will be difficult to get used to a low mattress with hard surface.
“Well, all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained to me that they couldn’t sleep properly here.”
"For their shrunken shoulders, heels and hips, they simply need a soft layer of visco-foam (Memory Foam - a shape-memory polymer)."
“I also recommend this to people with diabetes who suffer from a disorder of the nervous system, so that they can receive the “information” from the joints and skin badly,” explains Sylva Hadamczikov<0xC3><0xA1>, who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That’s why I have already provided these mattresses with visco-foam (memory foam) to many ice hockey players, as well as other customers, years ago.
"Today this is no longer a problem, because such mattresses offer, among others, the manufacturer Tempur, the Italian company Magniflex or the Czech manufacturer Tropico."
And you don’t necessarily have to be a famous ice hockey player to appreciate the benefits of visco-foam.
This "miracle" actually works quite simply.
The foam optimizes its hardness and shape according to the absorbed heat, in other words, it fits exactly on the warm body.
Nowhere does it press, at night you don’t roll around like after a hard fight.
You just sleep a lot better.
The viscoelastic foam also offers protection against decubitus (wound burning).
When choosing the mattress size, you should still add to the body size the length of the soles of the feet, that is, about 21 to 34 cm.
Both men and women, who are 180 cm tall, need a bed that is 210 to 220 cm long.
Each of the sleepers should be at least 90 cm wide, so together 180 cm.
For single beds, for example, for singles, 120 to 140 cm are attached.
For the sake of comfort and also for any visitors.
Otherwise, the following rule of thumb applies to the ideal width of the bed: "If you are lying on your back, there should still be enough room for the slightly angled arms", advises Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>, the craftsman of upholsterers and room decorators, who for years has been familiar with the problem of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of this furniture.
With a double bed, everyone needs their own grate and their own mattress, but be careful when shopping so that the mattresses are the same height.
Otherwise, there is nothing left but to mount the grate at different heights and this is not possible with every bed frame.
Foam mattresses should be at least 14 cm high, mattresses with spring skeleton 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters should be on the mold layer and the fine padding.
"With your hand or when you sit down, you should not feel the feathers in any way," warns Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>.
Each mattress requires a special type of rust.
Fully upholstered beds with mattress and underlay like cots have nothing to look for in the bedroom.
These mattresses can not be ventilated and the cover can not be washed, which is already happening today.
And since you lose between 0.2 and 0.75 liters of sweat in a single night, it is clear that after five to seven years, the mattress slowly becomes a huge (and clogged) screen.
Also for this reason, professionals reject advertising slogans that promise a lifetime of up to 25 years for mattresses, even a lifetime guarantee.
Every thing has its ifs and buts.
And therefore a practical advice from the dealers: For mattresses of 120 or 140 cm width, one should not shy away from the hygiene of the washable, removable covers, nevertheless, it is recommended to use a mattress protector, which can be easily removed and washed.
Even though today usually mattress covers with round zippers are made, so that after opening you get two halves (immensely important for the washing process and the size of the washing machine!), manipulation with larger mattresses, especially executed alone, often suggests the unequal struggle between David and Goliath.
Do they have a fixed plate in bed instead of a grate?
Get out of here!
Or at most for a bed for unloved guests and for a single night.
Also, they should preferably provide the plate with ventilation holes (unless they are already inside) and use mattresses with spring skeleton and a minimum height of 15 cm with so-called pocket springs and fine cushions.
Polyurethane mattresses do not belong on such a substrate.
For non-adjustable slats with 14 to 18 spring strips (slats), latex or sandwich mattresses are suitable (possibly also combinations of latex and coconut), always paying for slats with a larger number of slats, i.e. from 28 and more spring strips, with lordose support in the lumbar region and the possibility to regulate the slat hardness.
Adjustable slat grilles do not include mattresses with spring skeleton, as they do not respond to the ergonomic adjustment.
In addition to the adjustment of the stiffness of the spring strips, special flexible shoulder modules are also offered.
This involves a special fastening of the spring strips, which allows the spring strips to be pressed in or even angled in such a way that they allow the punctual sinking of the shoulder of the sleeper.
Especially for men with broad shoulders an important thing.
There are even mattress manufacturers who have started to use soft zones for the shoulder area in "men's mattresses".
The ladies are also meant - they are given these soft zones in the hip area.
For the most demanding customers, point-elastic spring systems (lattoflex) or grids with point-elastic contact pads with so-called multitorsion suspension are intended.
The pressure is distributed to several points, which reduces the voltage.
But - if you use a bad (too large and full) pillow for the right mattress and proper rust, most of the benefits are lost again.
Here, too, a rule of thumb: the pillow should support the head, its tips should only reach up to the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can relax.
Ideally, therefore, a 50 x 60 cm pillow, as the Scandinavians like it, for example, will appear.
In the side position, the pillow should balance the shoulder height (along with the shoulder relief zone in the grate or the soft zone in the mattress).
Our modern mattresses have something in common with the former (with hay filled) straw bags.
Modern manufacturers are increasingly using natural materials or at least their admixtures.
Even with mattresses, the new magic word is "bio".
Instead of petroleum raw materials, natural oils are increasingly used to produce polyurethane foams – for example castor and soy oil.
Soybeans are used by all known manufacturers.
“Bio is the name of mattresses, whose core is made of materials of pure natural origin,” explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek from Tropico Plus.
However, natural materials are also used in the production of mattress covers - one of the first was aloe vera.
However, it is also possible to treat microcapsules that spread fresh forest or lavender scent while sleeping.
Here, too, a difference is made between a man and a woman.
While in men a "cooling" plant extract from birch leaves is used so that the mattress cover can absorb the heat and cool the body, the covers for women have "warming" effect.
Extracts from red pepper shoots stimulate blood circulation, so the weaker sex gets comfortable warm while sleeping.
And today's favorites?
Cold foam mattresses (it has larger pores with destroyed cell structure and is therefore more breathable than commercial polyurethane and also much more flexible).
By combining the different stiffness (hardness) of cold foams and visco foams, multi-zone mattresses are created that know exactly where the head, hips and heels are located.
