While the Department of Justice officially refused to disclose the reasons for the decision in the Ensign case, Mr. Brand and other ethics lawyers said the Department appears to be very cautious in taking up political charges following a variety of defeats that were pursued by the media with great interest, including last year's decision to drop charges against the former Sen.
