Last year, when information about this affair was first released to the public, Mr. Ensign apologized to his constituents and gave up his position in the Senate, where he had been ranked fourth in the Republican ranking.
After noticing him for many months, Mr. Ensign told reporters two weeks ago that he was seeking a third term in the Senate.
Announcing that Mr. Ensign is no longer the target of police investigations, his spokeswoman, Jennifer Cooper, said the senator hoped the ethics committee would very quickly follow the Justice Department’s lead and stop its investigations.
“Senator Ensign is looking forward to continuing his hard work at the service of the people of Nevada,” she said.
