Early next year, the court will try Nuon Chea, Khieu Samphan, Ieng Sary and his wife, as well as Ieng Thirith, another former Khmer Rouge minister, in court.
The court’s order is to convict the old leaders and those primarily responsible for the atrocities, but it is not said whether it will pursue further acts beyond these four cases.
This has contributed little to alleviating the anxieties in Anlong Veng.
